      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a robust version that treats any exception as a distinct \"result\" and ignores the value of boolean success/failure to prevent crashes:\n\n```python\nimport random\nfrom collections import Counter\n\ndef detect_flakiness(func, n_runs=10):\n    results = Counter()\n    for _ in range(n_runs):\n        try:\n            result = func()\n            results.add(str(type(result).__name__))\n        except Exception:\n            # Treat any exception as a unique stability marker\n            results.add('exception')\n    \n    # Consider it flaky if there is more than one unique outcome type\n    return len(results) > 1\n\ndef test_exception_flaky():\n    if random.random() < 0.5:\n        return True\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(\"connection error\")\n\ndef test_always_error():\n    raise ValueError(\"always fails\")\n\nassert detect_flakiness(test_exception_flaky, 10) == True\nassert detect_flakiness(test_always_error, 10) == False\n\nprint(\"All tests passed!\")\n```\n\nThis solution normalizes different data types (integers, booleans, strings) to a string",
